        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "Bebe Nanki Laadli Beti Kalyan Scheme was launched by the Government of Punjab in 2011 with the objective of improving the gender ratio in the state. The scheme is a significant initiative aimed at preventing female foeticide and promoting the education and welfare of girl children. It provides financial assistance to eligible families at different stages to reduce the financial burden associated with the birth and upbringing of a girl child. Girls born on or after 1 January 2011 in the state of Punjab are eligible to avail the benefits of this scheme. Families with an annual income of less than ₹30,000 qualify for the scheme. To date, more than 26,000 beneficiaries have been covered under the Bebe Nanki Laadli Beti Kalyan Scheme.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Benefits**\nFinancial assistance of Rs.61,000 to the Guardian of Girl Child in different stages up to the age of 18 years. \nS NoPeriod of benefitAgeThe amount released by LIC to the guardian of the beneficiary1On the birth of newly born girl child0 years₹ 2,100/-2On attaining the age of 3 years (after full immunization)3 years₹ 2,100/-3On admission to Class -16 years₹ 2100/-4On admission to Class –IX14 years₹ 2,100/-5On attaining age of 18 years &amp;amp;amp;amp; passed Class- XII18 years₹ 3,1000/-6Scholarship payable-(a)From class-1 to VI standard 100/- per month-₹ 7,200/-(b)From class-VI1 to XII standard 200/- per month-₹ 14,400/-Total benefitAt the age of 18 years₹ 61,000/-<br>\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "**Exclusions**\n\n- This benefit will not be given to newly born boys. This benefit will not be given to newly born boys. \n\n",
        "briefDescription": "Bebe Nanki Laadli Beti Kalyan Scheme was launched under the 13th Finance Commission component for \"measures to improve gender ratio\" in the Punjab State from 2011-12. ",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "align_justify",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bebe Nanki Laadli Beti Kalyan Scheme was launched by the Government of Punjab in 2011 with the objective of improving the gender ratio in the state. The scheme is a significant initiative aimed at preventing female foeticide and promoting the education and welfare of girl children. It provides financial assistance to eligible families at different stages to reduce the financial burden associated with the birth and upbringing of a girl child. Girls born on or after 1 January 2011 in the state of Punjab are eligible to avail the benefits of this scheme. Families with an annual income of less than ₹30,000 qualify for the scheme. To date, more than 26,000 beneficiaries have been covered under the Bebe Nanki Laadli Beti Kalyan Scheme."
                  }
                ]
              }
